Package org.coronabounce.models

Class Population

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.coronabounce.models.Population
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Displayable
    public class Population
extends Object
implements Displayable
    Population consists of individuals which move (CoquilleBilles) and participate in epidemy.

      • saveStatToData

        public void saveStatToData()
        Transfers NbSick and NbRecovered to Data to save them to draw AreaChart. To show correctly superposed layers in AreaChart we take:
        • NbHealthy taken as 100% (bottom layer)
        • nbSick = nbSick + NbIncubating + nbRecovered (middle layer)
        • NbRecovered = NbRecovered (top layer)
        Superposed they present ratio of these tree values (nbHealthy, nbSick/Incubating and nbRecovered) in 100%.
        Specified by:
        saveStatToData in interface Displayable

        Specified by:

        Parameters:
